body:
## Motivation

The release notes for 0.6-rc.1 contains the following code:
```
// implement `FromRequestParts` if you don't need to consume the request body
#[async_trait]
impl<S> FromRequestParts<S> for MyExtractor
where
    S: Send + Sync,
    B: Send + 'static,
{
    type Rejection = StatusCode;

    async fn from_request_parts(parts: &mut Parts, state: &S) -> Result<Self, Self::Rejection> {
        // ...
    }
}
```

`B: Send + 'static` cannot compile as `B` is not known for this implementation.

## Solution

Remove `B: Send + 'static`.

This ports `#[derive(FromRequest)]` to the new traits.

It always implements `FromRequest` (we might want `#[derive(FromRequestParts)]` but that can be done separately) and only allows the last field to implement `FromRequest`. I.e.:

```rust
// doesn't work
// #[derive(FromRequest)]
// struct Foo {
//     body: String,
//     ext: Extension<bool>,
// }

// does work
#[derive(FromRequest)]
struct Foo {
    ext: Extension<bool>,
    body: String,
}
```

This probably isn't the most intuitive thing ever but the compile error is good so should be pretty clear. Its also documented.

I also ran into some issues with generating custom rejections. Specifically you do something like this

```rust
#[derive(FromRequest)]
struct Foo {
    ext: Extension<bool>,
    body: String,
}
```

We'd generate a rejection like this

```rust
enum FooRejection {
    Ext(<Extension<bool> as FromRequest<(), Body>>::Rejection),
    Body(<String as FromRequest<(), Body>>::Rejection),
}
```

However `<Extension<bool> as FromRequest<(), Body>>::Rejection` doesn't work because like we've seen before `Extension` doesn't implement `FromRequest<(), Body, /* Once */>`, it implements `FromRequest<(), Body, Mut>`.

Not sure there is a solution to this so I just decided to not generate custom rejections and instead use `Rejection = Response`. If users want their own rejection type they can use

```rust
#[derive(FromRequest)]
#[from_request(rejection(MyRejection))]
struct Foo {
    ext: Extension<bool>,
    body: String,
}

enum MyRejection { ... }
```

That also simplifies our code a ton because we don't need all the `#[from_request(rejection_derive(!Display, !Error)]` stuff.
